-- U.S. Stocks Pare Losses as Banks Rally Following Fed's Decision
-- B y   N i c k   B a k e r
-- 2010-11-03T18:51:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/stocks-in-u-s-pare-losses-as-banks-rally-following-fed-stimulus-decision.html
U.S. stocks pared losses as banks
rallied following the Federal Reserve’s plan to purchase $600
billion of Treasuries through June.  The  Standard & Poor’s 500 Index  fell 0.1 percent to
1,191.85 at 2:50 p.m. in New York after dropping as much as 0.8
percent in the minutes after the Fed’s announcement. Financial
shares in the index rallied 0.3 percent, the most among 10
industries.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at 
 nbaker7@bloomberg.net  